webpackJsonp([0x7500c6e3ab9f],{526:function(e,t){e.exports={pathContext:{frontmatter:{path:"/docs/aspect-ratio",title:"Aspect Ratio",hasPlayground:!0,initialPlayground:null,redirect:null},html:'<h2>Aspect Ratio</h2>\n<p>AspectRatio is a property introduced by Yoga and is not present as a settable\nproperty in the css flexbox specification. Flexbox does has the notion of\naspect ratio though for things with intrinsic aspect ratio such as images.</p>\n<p>The <code class="language-text">aspect ratio</code> property in Yoga has the following properties:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Accepts any floating point value > 0, the default is undefined.</li>\n<li>Defined as the ratio between the <code class="language-text">width</code> and the <code class="language-text">height</code> of a node e.g. if a node has an aspect ratio of 2 then its <code class="language-text">width</code> is twice the size of its <code class="language-text">height</code>.</li>\n<li>Respects the <code class="language-text">min</code> and <code class="language-text">max</code> dimensions of an item.</li>\n<li>Has higher priority than <code class="language-text">flex grow</code></li>\n<li>If <code class="language-text">aspect ratio</code>, <code class="language-text">width</code>, and <code class="language-text">height</code> are set then the cross axis dimension is overridden.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><controls prop="aspectRatio"></controls></p>'}}}});
